com.facebook.buck.event

Class FlushConsoleEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.event.AbstractBuckEvent
      • com.facebook.buck.event.FlushConsoleEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BuckEvent, BuckEventExternalInterface

    public class FlushConsoleEvent
extends AbstractBuckEvent
    Event to tell the console that it needs to flush now. This is used to ensure that all pending events are written before potentially writing to stdout (which would cause certain event busses to cease rendering)

    Use of this class is generally an antipattern, and is only used currently to make up for some shortcomings in SuperConsoleEventBusListener
